author: George Rede | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Police investigating death of man found at I-5 rest area near Wilsonville
text:
Update: Detectives interview a person of interest in rest area death
Oregon State Police late Monday were investigating the death of a man who was found with traumatic injuries at the French Prairie rest area (formerly Baldock rest area) just off Interstate 5 near Wilsonville.
Troopers and medical personnel responded about 8:26 p.m. to a report of a man found injured at the southbound rest area, state police said. Paramedics were unable to save the man and he died at the scene, police said.
Troopers closed the rest area while conducting the investigation and said just after 11 p.m. that they had no further information.
This post will be updated as more details become available.
